342#define DNS_RESULT_RESULTSET 2
343#define DNS_RESULT_RCODERESULTSET 3
344
345static isc_once_t once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;
346
347static void
348initialize_action(void) {
349 isc_result_t result;
350
351 result = isc_result_register(ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNS, DNS_R_NRESULTS,
352 text, DNS_RESULT_RESULTSET);
353 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
354 result = isc_result_register(ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE,
355 DNS_R_NRCODERESULTS,
356 rcode_text,
357 DNS_RESULT_RCODERESULTSET);
358 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
359 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
360 "isc_result_register() failed: %u", result);
361
362 result = isc_result_registerids(ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNS, DNS_R_NRESULTS,
363 ids, DNS_RESULT_RESULTSET);
364 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
365 result = isc_result_registerids(ISC_RESULTCLASS_DNSRCODE,
366 DNS_R_NRCODERESULTS,
367 rcode_ids,
368 DNS_RESULT_RCODERESULTSET);
369 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
370 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
371 "isc_result_registerids() failed: %u", result);
372}
373
374static void
375initialize(void) {
376 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, initialize_action) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
377}
378
379const char *
380dns_result_totext(isc_result_t result) {
381 initialize();
382
383 return (isc_result_totext(result));
384}
385
386void
387dns_result_register(void) {
388 initialize();
389}
390
391dns_rcode_t
392dns_result_torcode(isc_result_t result) {
393 dns_rcode_t rcode = dns_rcode_servfail;
394
395 if (DNS_RESULT_ISRCODE(result)) {
396 /*
397 * Rcodes can't be bigger than 12 bits, which is why we
398 * AND with 0xFFF instead of 0xFFFF.
399 */
400 return ((dns_rcode_t)((result) & 0xFFF));
401 }
402
403 /*
404 * Try to supply an appropriate rcode.
405 */
406 switch (result) {
407 case ISC_R_SUCCESS:
408 rcode = dns_rcode_noerror;
409 break;
410 case ISC_R_BADBASE64:
411 case ISC_R_RANGE:
412 case ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND:
413 case DNS_R_BADAAAA:
414 /* case DNS_R_BADBITSTRING: deprecated */
415 case DNS_R_BADCKSUM:
416 case DNS_R_BADCLASS:
417 case DNS_R_BADLABELTYPE:
418 case DNS_R_BADPOINTER:
419 case DNS_R_BADTTL:
420 case DNS_R_BADZONE:
421 /* case DNS_R_BITSTRINGTOOLONG: deprecated */
422 case DNS_R_EXTRADATA:
423 case DNS_R_LABELTOOLONG:
424 case DNS_R_NOREDATA:
425 case DNS_R_SYNTAX:
426 case DNS_R_TEXTTOOLONG:
427 case DNS_R_TOOMANYHOPS:
428 case DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET:
429 case DNS_R_UNKNOWN:
430 case DNS_R_NAMETOOLONG:
431 case DNS_R_OPTERR:
432 rcode = dns_rcode_formerr;
433 break;
434 case DNS_R_DISALLOWED:
435 rcode = dns_rcode_refused;
436 break;
437 case DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE:
438 case DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW:
439 rcode = dns_rcode_notauth;
440 break;
441 default:
442 rcode = dns_rcode_servfail;
443 }
444
445 return (rcode);
446}
